The code For parts 1,3,4,5 is under the file: tagger1.py
to run the code First:
activate a conda env Using
conda create -n "myenv" python=3.8
pip install -r requirements.txt

Once you actiavte the env run:
You will need to have the data files unzipped under data/pos and data/ner
and have  preprocessing.py
under the progarm base dir
Task: {pos, ner}
Part: {1,3,4,5}
optimizer: {SGD, Adam, AdamW}
batch_size: int
l_r: float
hidden_dim: int
filter_num: (for part 5 only ) int
window_size: (for part 5 only ) int

The usage is as follow using standart argparse:
main.py --task TASK --part PART [--optimizer OPTIMIZER] [--batch_size BATCH_SIZE] [--l_r L_R] --hidden_dim
               HIDDEN_DIM [--filter_num FILTER_NUM] [--window_size WINDOW_SIZE]
			   
